	<h1><strong>Major Awards, Achievements & Recognitions</strong></h1>
<p>Raghava published more than 200 research papers in reputed journals, developed 25 currated databases, 80 copyrights and 200 web servers. Following are major achievements.</p>
<ol><li><a href="https://www.facebook.com/IIITDelhi/posts/2064098920273794">Felicitated by the Uttar Pradesh Govt.</a>&nbsp; : U.P. Govt. felicitate G. P. S. Raghava on U.P. Divas on 26th January 2018.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li>
<li><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=V-0BTIKH78E">Eureka with G P S Raghava</a>&nbsp;: Under Eureka programme Raghava's interview was telecast on Rajya Sabha TV on 20th &amp; 21st June 2015 (A programme that brings life-time story and outstanding scientific contribution of a scientist).&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li>
<li><a href="http://highlycited.com/">Highly Cited Researchers 2014</a>&nbsp;(Top 1% researchers): G P S Raghava has been listed in&nbsp;<a href="http://sciencewatch.com/sites/sw/files/sw-article/media/worlds-most-influential-scientific-minds-2014.pdf">The World's Most Influential Scientific Minds</a>&nbsp;by Thompson Reuters (News:&nbsp;<a href="http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chandigarh/Change-head8-Indians-pale-in-comparison-with-163-Chinese-in-list-of-highly-cited-researchers/articleshow/38983168.cms">Times of India</a>&nbsp;,&nbsp;<a href="http://webs.iiitd.edu.in/raghava/news/pu_thomson.pdf">PU News</a>).&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li>
<li><a href="http://www.dailypioneer.com/home/online-channel/296-business/112252-president-for-increasing-enrolment-in-higher-education.pdf">Young Leader Award</a>&nbsp;in Science &amp; Technology,&nbsp;<a href="http://www.jklakshmi.com/pdf/press-release_IIML-national-leadership-awards-nov-30-2012.pdf">Lakshmipat Singhania - IIM Lucknow National Leadership awards 2011</a>&nbsp;(News:&nbsp;<a href="http://webs.iiitd.edu.in/raghava/news/bios_award.pdf">Biospectrum Award</a>&nbsp;,&nbsp;<a href="http://webs.iiitd.edu.in/raghava/news/Bios_raghava.pdf">Bioinformatician</a>).&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li>
<li><a href="http://www.scribd.com/doc/177534075/Great-Indian-Scientists-Tell-Me-Why-81-Gnv64#scribd">Raghava name listed in&nbsp;<strong>Great Indian Scientists</strong>&nbsp;(Tell Me Why #81, published by MANORAMA, 2013)</a>.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li>
<li>One paper listed in top 70 highly cited papers (ranked 18) published by CSIR scientists in last 70 years .&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li>
<li><a href="http://webs.iiitd.edu.in/raghava/news/bose.html">Prestigious JC Bose National Fellowship 2010</a>.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li>
<li><a href="http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/holnus/000200809261647.htm">Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Awards 2008</a>&nbsp;in Biological Sciences.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li>
<li><a href="http://nasi.nic.in/NASI-Reliance%20Industries%20Platinum%20Jubilee%20Awardees%20(2009).htm">NASI-Reliance Industries Platinum Jubilee Awards,</a>&nbsp;2009 in Biological Sciences.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li>
<li>Ranked 18 in highly cited papers published by CSIR scientists in last 70 years (1942-2012)&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li>
<li>Thomson Reuters Research Excellence -&nbsp;<a href="http://ip-science.thomsonreuters.com/ssr/researchday_09_in/">India Research Front Awards 2009</a>.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li>
<li>National Bioscience Award of year 2005-6 for career development by&nbsp;<a href="http://dbtindia.nic.in/awardees/awardmain.html">Department of Biotechnology&nbsp;</a>(Govt. of India) New Delhi.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li>
<li>Fellow of the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.ias.ac.in/">Indian Academy of Sciences, Banglore</a>&nbsp;for his excellent contribution in the field of Bioinformatics&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li>
<li>Fellow of National Academy of Sciences by "<a href="http://nasi.nic.in/">The National Academy of Sciences, India</a>" for his excellent contribution in the field of Bioinformatics.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li>
<li>Ranked&nbsp;<a href="http://www.bio-computing.org/labs.php?start=25&amp;score=totalscore&amp;status=lab&amp;search=">30th among worldwide bioinformatics heads</a>&nbsp;and 1st in indian bioinformatics heads.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li>
<li><a href="http://www.biomedcentral.com/profiles/authorindex/?action=display&amp;id=768661229249686">Listed as a&nbsp;</a><a href="http://www.biomedcentral.com/profiles/hot100/">hot 100 authors by BioMed Central</a>&nbsp;for his contributions.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li>
<li><a href="http://scholar.google.co.in/citations?hl=en&amp;user=XK5GUiYAAAAJ">Raghava has H-index 41 with more than 5300 citations</a>&nbsp;in Jan 2014 as per&nbsp;<a href="http://scholar.google.com/citations?user=XK5GUiYAAAAJ&amp;hl=en">google scholar</a>&nbsp;.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li>
<li>Associate Editor of&nbsp;<a href="http://www.biomedcentral.com/bmcresnotes/">BMC Research Notes</a>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li>
<li>Associate Editor of&nbsp;<a href="http://www.biomedcentral.com/bmcbioinformatics/">BMC Bioinformatics</a>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li>
<li>Academic Editor of&nbsp;<a href="http://www.plosone.org/">Plos One</a>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li>
<li>Member of editorial board of number of journals.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li>
<li>Research fellowship (1984-86) was awarded by IIT Delhi, after qualifying national test GATE.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li>
<li>BBSRC fellowship, funded by UK for postdoctoral studies at Oxford University, UK from 1996 to 1998.&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li>
<li>Invited by University of Arkansas for Medical Sciences (UAMS), Little Rock, USA to establish Bioinformatics (<a href="http://bioinformatics.uams.edu/">http://bioinformatics.uams.edu/)</a>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li>
<li>Visiting Professorship for six months (March 2004 to August 2004) to initiate Bioinformatics activities at Pohang University of Science and Technolgy (POSTECH).&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li>
<li>Methods developed at group successfully participate and ranked in top methods in the world in international competitions like CASP, CAFASP and EVA.<br>

<br><br>
<h2><strong>Technology</strong></h2></li>
<li>Raghava was a key figure in the development&nbsp;&nbsp;of BioSuite which is a bioinformatics software developed by TCS with experts in bioinformatics under NMITLI programmee. This package has been launched by Honable President of India Dr APJ Abdul Kalam, on 14<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;July 2004 (News:&nbsp;<a href="http://www.thehindu.com/2004/07/15/stories/2004071515010500.htm">The Hindu</a>).&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;</li>
<li>In collaboration with private company Biomantra a software package VaxiPred: Computer aided vaccine design, was developed. This package has been launched by Director General, CSIR Dr R A Mashlekar on 15<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;of December 2004 (News:&nbsp;<a href="http://webs.iiitd.edu.in/raghava/news/vaxipred_telegraph.pdf">The Telegraph&nbsp;</a>.</li>
</ol></td>

</div>
